  "text": "Examined through the lens of this scholarship, one explanation for the increasing dominance of market-based interventions in conservation could be the emergence of an epistemic community, actively promoting the adoption of such approaches during the last two decades. [CITATION_1] suggests that such a community, a 'transnational conservation elite' that shares, replicates, amplifies, and promotes ideas about market-based solutions to the conservation community is emergent, but Holmes does not provide empirical evidence indicating the existence of such a transnational conservation elite.",
